 from the eighth Federal Congress for Cultural Politics, entitled "Kultur.Macht.Einheit?" ("Culture.Power.Unity?"), which featured presentations be figures such as Monika Grütters, Wolfgang Thierse, Norbert Lammert, and Tim Renner. Additional articles extrapolate on this extensive field and broaden the range of perspectives on the phenomenon of transformation.  afunded by Beauftragte der Bundesregierung für Kultur und Medien  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPolitical science. 4aDeutsche Einheit. 4aGeschichte der Kulturpolitik. 4aGesellschaftlicher Wandel. 4aKultur. 4aKulturförderung. 4aKulturmanagement. 4aPolitik. 4aTransformation. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Management.2bisacsh  aCultural Funding.  aCultural Management.  aCulture.  aGerman Unity.  aPolitics.  aSocial Change.  aTransformation.1 aAnders, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBisky, Jens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBittner, Regina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBolwin, Rolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraun, Eckhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuschmann, Lara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarp, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDieckmann, Friedrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDümcke, Cornelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFitz, Angelika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/r